WEBVTT

00:05.370 --> 00:07.031
MAN: That's all that happened.
I was sitting over there,
minding my...

00:07.070 --> 00:08.332
Sir, all I'm
asking...

00:08.370 --> 00:09.667
all I'm asking...
I did nothing wrong.

00:09.710 --> 00:11.166
And I didn't say you
did anything wrong.

00:11.210 --> 00:13.235
There was no sign saying
I couldn't sit in that area.

00:13.280 --> 00:15.202
I just need to know what
the problem was back there.
The problem was I'm black.

00:15.240 --> 00:17.105
Hey, sir.
No, seriously,
all I was doing was

00:17.150 --> 00:18.401
I need you to
calm down.
sitting there
until it was time

00:18.450 --> 00:20.042
to pick up my wife
and kids.
Sir?

00:20.080 --> 00:21.445
MAN:
What's happening, buddy?

00:21.480 --> 00:23.539
Nothing, I've got to go
pick up my wife and kids.

00:23.590 --> 00:26.058
MAN: No, you're
under arrest.
What? _I-I didn't
do anything wrong.

00:26.090 --> 00:28.354
Put your hands
behind your back.
Please take
your hands off me.

00:28.390 --> 00:31.154
(all three talking
over each other)

00:31.190 --> 00:32.555
Put your hands
behind your back.

00:32.600 --> 00:34.420
Hey, I did nothing wrong,
all right?

00:34.460 --> 00:36.428
Don't make me
use this.
Oh, now you're
gonna shoot me?

00:36.470 --> 00:38.062
I said...
For what? For...

00:38.100 --> 00:41.069
(all three talking
over each other)

00:41.100 --> 00:42.761
(Taser buzzing)
No, don't do it.

00:42.810 --> 00:44.232
WOMAN: No!
(screams)

00:44.270 --> 00:46.636
No! Oh, my God!

00:46.680 --> 00:48.739
You're killing me.
Cole!

00:48.780 --> 00:50.748
NEWSCASTER: Tonight, a jury
continues to hear evidence

00:50.780 --> 00:53.078
about the death of Cole Willis.

00:53.120 --> 00:55.714
Willis' death at the hands
of two police officers,

00:55.750 --> 00:58.116
Michael and Trenton,
places Chicago

00:58.150 --> 01:01.608
on a growing list of cities
protesting racial injustice

01:01.660 --> 01:03.321
by local law enforcement.

01:03.360 --> 01:05.157
JOSH: You'll definitely
be asked about this.

01:05.190 --> 01:06.555
Are these two cops guilty
of, you know,

01:06.600 --> 01:08.352
involuntary
manslaughter?

01:08.400 --> 01:10.197
Well, I can't comment on it--
the trial's still going on.

01:10.230 --> 01:10.969
_ It's _not
still gomg on.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.297
I have a friend
in the courthouse.

01:12.340 --> 01:14.262
The judge just finished
jury instructions.

01:14.300 --> 01:16.165
Geez, talk about the luck.
ALICIA: Well, I still
can't comment on it.

01:16.210 --> 01:18.838
Uh, Prady won't have any problem
commenting on it-- he wants

01:18.870 --> 01:20.633
the black vote, he will
play up the, you know,
the blah-blah-blah.

01:20.680 --> 01:22.307
Here, let me take the jacket.

01:22.350 --> 01:24.147
Excuse me, can you do
this another time?
She goes on

01:24.180 --> 01:26.273
in 20 minutes. When do you
advise I take in the arms?

01:26.320 --> 01:27.742
If you want something to eat,
I can make you a sandwich.

01:27.780 --> 01:28.849
No, nothing to eat, it'll make
her want to throw up onstage.

01:28.880 --> 01:30.245
How about peanuts?

01:30.290 --> 01:31.439
No, now go away,
crazy lady!

01:31.490 --> 01:32.479
Okay, okay, okay, just listen.

01:32.520 --> 01:34.215
You show support
to the police,

01:34.260 --> 01:36.251
but you also argue the best way
to support the police...

01:36.290 --> 01:37.587
And let's lose the necklace.

01:37.630 --> 01:39.222
It's less fussy.
Why didn't you
do this before?

01:39.260 --> 01:40.352
I need to see
it on the body.

01:40.400 --> 01:43.494
Okay, we have 18 minutes to go,
let's hold it together.

01:43.530 --> 01:44.622
Josh, step away for a second.

01:44.670 --> 01:46.160
Me. I'm the only one
doing my job.

01:46.200 --> 01:48.361
Okay, take a breath.
Where's Jon?

01:48.400 --> 01:50.209
VVho?
Elfman.

01:50.240 --> 01:51.207
Oh, I don't know.

01:51.240 --> 01:52.707
He'll be here. Why?

01:52.740 --> 01:53.877
Never mind.

01:53.910 --> 01:55.434
Take a breath.

01:55.480 --> 01:57.607
Okay, the bad news is
you're six points down.

01:57.650 --> 02:00.369
The good news is this is
your chance to take it to him.

02:00.420 --> 02:01.910
Okay?

02:01.950 --> 02:03.178
Prady won't be
expecting it.

02:03.220 --> 02:04.346
We've lowered
expectations.

02:04.390 --> 02:05.482
So don't be afraid
to interrupt him.

02:05.520 --> 02:06.589
Tell him,
"That's not true!"

02:06.620 --> 02:07.712
She's eight
points down.

02:07.760 --> 02:09.284
She needs to
shake you.

02:09.330 --> 02:11.286
She'll interrupt you,
try to get you

02:12.830 --> 02:14.491
Right, just roll with the
punches, you're the frontrunner.

02:14.530 --> 02:16.498
Give off the air
of the frontrunner,

02:16.530 --> 02:18.168
she'll look desperate.

02:18.200 --> 02:19.337
He's a stickler
for rules.

02:19.370 --> 02:20.439
He'll complain
to the moderator,

02:20.470 --> 02:21.494
and that'll make him
look small.

02:21.540 --> 02:22.336
Uh-oh, you're
getting a call

02:22.370 --> 02:24.463
from work, a client.
No, not right now.

02:24.510 --> 02:25.738
What are you doing?
We're in countdown mode.

02:25.770 --> 02:27.533
She has to focus.
They say
it's important.

02:27.580 --> 02:28.831
Okay, just take a message,
I'll call them back.

02:28.880 --> 02:29.904
It's Neil Gross.

02:29.950 --> 02:30.905
Uh-oh.
No.
Oh.

02:30.950 --> 02:32.178
I have to take it.

02:32.220 --> 02:33.175
He's our biggest client.

02:33.220 --> 02:34.517
Just give me a second.
Alicia!

02:34.550 --> 02:35.949
ALICIA:
What's the problem, Mr. Gross?

02:35.980 --> 02:37.641
Yeah,
they're saying $30 million.

02:37.690 --> 02:38.941
$30 million.

02:38.990 --> 02:40.514
I thought I said no higher
than $15 million.

02:40.560 --> 02:41.959
Uh, you did say $15 million.

02:41.990 --> 02:43.480
Who's saying $30 million?

02:43.530 --> 02:44.679
I don't know, some guy,
your lawyer.

02:44.730 --> 02:46.322
I don't even know who he is.

02:46.360 --> 02:47.520
Um, Evan?
Oh, Evan.

02:47.560 --> 02:49.528
Yeah, he's a...
he's a good lawyer.

02:49.570 --> 02:51.629
Yeah, well, you need
to protect me-- I have a prenup.

02:51.670 --> 02:53.558
I don't know why I'm paying
an arm and a leg.

02:53.600 --> 02:55.534
Just so you know, Alicia,
I'm thinking about leaving.

02:55.570 --> 02:56.798
Oh, don't do that, Mr. Gross.

02:56.840 --> 02:58.569
Why? You're running for office.

02:58.610 --> 03:00.976
I don't even... I don't even
recognize these people.

03:01.010 --> 03:03.274
Come on, get your clothes
on.
Okay, let me look into it,
and I'll get back to you.

03:03.310 --> 03:04.470
Good.

03:04.510 --> 03:05.602
I'm unhappy.

03:05.650 --> 03:06.947
Let's put this down here,
we don't want

03:06.980 --> 03:08.277
to make it look like
you're trying too hard.

03:08.320 --> 03:09.446
There's been
a last-minute change--

03:09.490 --> 03:10.445
we need to show
you something.

03:10.490 --> 03:11.445
All right, I just need a second.

03:11.490 --> 03:12.411
Alicia, it's eight minutes

03:12.460 --> 03:14.280
until you go on.
And they changed
the clock.

03:14.320 --> 03:15.958
You know, the, uh, the, um,
you know, countdown thing.

03:15.990 --> 03:17.457
It's digital now.
Okay, I'll tell her,

03:17.490 --> 03:18.525
I'll tell her.
I need you to see it...

03:18.560 --> 03:21.324
Can I have Diane
or Cary, please?
It's digital now.

03:21.360 --> 03:24.568
Ah, thank you,
thank you so much.

03:24.600 --> 03:28.331
I have to confess, I feel
like I'm 60 years older.

03:28.370 --> 03:29.735
But I've missed
this,
WOMAN: Diane?

03:29.770 --> 03:30.759
I miss just-just
being,

03:30.810 --> 03:31.799
talking about
something

03:31.840 --> 03:33.808
other than going to prison.

03:33.840 --> 03:35.535
Um, but, uh,
yeah, it's been...

03:35.580 --> 03:36.649
It's Alicia.
I'm back now

03:36.680 --> 03:37.408
and I'm ready
to pitch in,

03:37.450 --> 03:38.576
so whatever
you guys need, just...

03:38.610 --> 03:40.316
Alicia, how are you?

03:40.350 --> 03:42.545
I think you're going on
in about two minutes.

03:42.590 --> 03:44.649
Yes, um, look, I just got
a call from Neil Gross.

03:44.690 --> 03:46.248
He's very upset about
his divorce settlement.

03:46.290 --> 03:48.281
He called you? Why?

03:48.320 --> 03:50.652
He said that Evan
is offering $30 million

03:50.690 --> 03:52.294
and he's threatening
to leave the firm.

03:52.330 --> 03:53.592
Well, this is a surprise to me.

03:53.630 --> 03:55.655
We agreed to go no higher
than $15 million.

03:55.700 --> 03:56.997
I know.

03:57.030 --> 03:58.793
There could be a chance
that Evan is freelancing.

03:58.830 --> 04:01.469
Look, I have to go on,
could you take care of it?

04:01.500 --> 04:02.728
Uh, yes. Good luck, kick ass.

04:02.770 --> 04:03.805
Kalinda, do you
have a minute?

04:03.840 --> 04:05.398
One second.
CARY:
What's wrong?

04:05.440 --> 04:06.805
I think you may
need to suit up

04:06.840 --> 04:08.330
soonerthan
you expected.

04:08.380 --> 04:10.007
My client is ruined, sir.

04:10.050 --> 04:11.506
GROSS:
She's not "ruined."

04:11.550 --> 04:12.744
She has the house
in Brentwood,

04:12.780 --> 04:13.974
the apartment in
San Francisco.

04:14.020 --> 04:16.443
Emotionally ruined,
scarred, distraught.

04:16.490 --> 04:17.980
WOMAN: You slept with my best
friend, I can't believe it.

04:18.020 --> 04:19.578
You slept with
my competitor.

04:19.620 --> 04:21.383
That was a pre-existing
relationship.

04:21.420 --> 04:22.728
GROSS: Which you
then renewed.
Where are we,
Evan?

04:22.760 --> 04:25.627
We're agreeing on an amount.

04:25.660 --> 04:26.888
And we said $30 million
isn't enough.

04:26.930 --> 04:28.727
$30 million? How did
we get to $30 million?

04:28.760 --> 04:30.022
We didn't get
to $30 million,

04:30.070 --> 04:31.992
your lawyer offered
$30 million, and we said

04:32.030 --> 04:33.463
that wasn't enough.
Why did you offer
$30 million?

04:33.500 --> 04:34.762
I'll show you why.

04:35.800 --> 04:37.062
Photos.

04:37.110 --> 04:39.829
You may want to avert
your eyes, dear.

04:39.880 --> 04:43.441
This is you, Mr. Gross,
in bed with your ski instructor.

04:43.480 --> 04:45.778
That's why your new head
of family law,

04:45.810 --> 04:48.643
the one you promoted
after I left,

04:48.680 --> 04:49.647
offered $30 million
to settle.

04:49.690 --> 04:52.386
Because these photos will not
look good on TMZ.

04:52.420 --> 04:54.615
CARY:
That's intimidation, Mr. Lee.

04:54.660 --> 04:56.855
A class three felony.
Yes, if I indeed
threatened you,

04:56.890 --> 04:58.881
but I did not.
I just know

04:58.930 --> 05:03.094
how salacious photos tend
to find their way onto the Web.

05:03.130 --> 05:05.394
Evan's always been our
toughest negotiator.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.398
I don't understand.

05:07.440 --> 05:08.668
What changed?

05:08.700 --> 05:10.668
Did David Lee hire
Evan originally?

05:10.710 --> 05:12.678
You think he's intimidated
by his old boss?

05:12.710 --> 05:14.337
I think he might be.
No.

05:14.380 --> 05:15.972
Could you give
me a half hour?

05:16.010 --> 05:17.739
CARY: Why?
What's going on?

05:17.780 --> 05:19.645
I think that David Lee is
offering him a job,

05:19.680 --> 05:22.342
but Evan's too afraid to bite
the hand that will feed him.

05:22.390 --> 05:24.711
(sighs) Okay, so we put
a pause in the negotiation,

05:24.750 --> 05:27.355
see if we should
replace Evan.

05:27.390 --> 05:28.516
What?

05:28.560 --> 05:29.720
I've missed this.

05:29.760 --> 05:32.058
All _the usual
disasters.

05:32.090 --> 05:33.557
WOMAN:
Do you want some water?

05:33.600 --> 05:34.828
You should hydrate.

05:34.860 --> 05:38.523
(everybody talking
over each other)

05:38.570 --> 05:40.834
MA_N:
HI.

05:40.870 --> 05:43.600
Chris Matthews. I am so
glad to be doing this.

05:43.640 --> 05:44.868
Oh, hello,
I'm so glad you could.

05:44.910 --> 05:46.537
With you two running
for state's attorney,

05:46.580 --> 05:47.706
how could I not?

05:47.740 --> 05:48.729
I'll see you
out there.

05:48.780 --> 05:50.748
ALICIA:
See you out there.

05:50.780 --> 05:52.077
Okay, I know, three minutes
till you're on.

05:52.110 --> 05:53.668
Here are the key
points again.

05:53.720 --> 05:54.675
Okay, wait, wait,
we've got a problem.

05:54.720 --> 05:56.449
I just got a call
from one of the reporters,

05:56.490 --> 05:57.514
and we got to think fast.

05:57.550 --> 05:59.552
Which one?
Patrick Mancini.

05:59.590 --> 06:00.352
With the, um,
Middeleton Herald.

06:00.390 --> 06:01.755
He's the one
on the end right there.

06:01.790 --> 06:02.825
ELI:
He's a real jackass.

06:02.860 --> 06:03.827
What does he want?

06:03.860 --> 06:05.748
He's, uh...

06:05.790 --> 06:07.997
got photos of the governor
with Ramona Lytton.

06:08.030 --> 06:09.827
Leaving her apartment.

06:09.870 --> 06:10.996
From when? When
were they taken?

06:11.030 --> 06:12.531
Uh, two days ago.

06:12.570 --> 06:13.992
He plans on making that
his first question.

06:14.040 --> 06:15.598
Eli, what is going on?

06:15.640 --> 06:16.834
I thought he
broke it off.

06:16.870 --> 06:18.838
Yeah, stuck it in
and broke it off.

06:18.870 --> 06:20.929
Okay, let's not jump
to conclusions.

06:20.980 --> 06:22.743
I will talk to him,
but in the meantime,

06:22.780 --> 06:23.974
I wouldn't rise
to the bait.

06:24.010 --> 06:24.840
How do we not
rise to the bait?

06:24.880 --> 06:25.744
He's got the whole
thing documented.

06:25.780 --> 06:27.645
Let my office deal
with this-- defer to us.

06:27.680 --> 06:28.749
We've got three minutes.
(cell phone buzzes)

06:28.780 --> 06:29.940
Uh, Alicia,
you're getting a call.

06:29.990 --> 06:31.719
No, not now.
Uh, from the governor.

06:31.750 --> 06:32.819
Don't take it.

06:32.860 --> 06:33.986
He probably got a call
from Mancini, too.

06:34.020 --> 06:35.556
There is nothing
you can say right now

06:35.590 --> 06:36.784
that'll make this
any easrer.
Just try and relax.

06:36.830 --> 06:38.786
ALICIA: I'm away
from my phone at the moment,

06:38.830 --> 06:40.798
so please leave a message.

06:40.830 --> 06:41.990
Are you ready,
Mr. Governor?

06:42.030 --> 06:43.520
Yes, I am, Pastor.

06:43.570 --> 06:45.128
And I want_t_o thank
you for InVItIng me.

06:45.170 --> 06:48.890
No, it's best if we can all
talk with one voice.

06:48.940 --> 06:51.465
Yes.
NEWSCASTER: The fate
of Officers Michael and Trenton

06:51.510 --> 06:53.501
are now in the hands of a jury.

06:53.540 --> 06:54.734
(cell phone rings)

06:54.780 --> 06:56.099
Um, can you just
give me one second?

06:56.140 --> 06:58.005
Eli, where are you?

06:58.050 --> 06:59.039
_ ELI:
ComIng to you.

07:01.520 --> 07:02.919
Don't answer any questions
about Ramona.

07:02.950 --> 07:04.918
They have photos
of the two of you.

07:04.950 --> 07:06.554
From when?

07:06.590 --> 07:08.182
Two nights ago.

07:08.220 --> 07:10.029
Have they asked Alicia about it?

07:10.060 --> 07:11.789
Not yet, but they
may in the debate.

07:11.830 --> 07:14.025
Just don't answer any calls,
let me work on this for a while.

07:14.060 --> 07:15.596
(cell phone buzzes)
It's Bill Duncan.

07:15.630 --> 07:17.598
Oh, great, it's reached
full saturation.

07:17.630 --> 07:19.598
Mr. Governor,
I'll be there in a minute.

07:19.640 --> 07:20.789
Bill, hey.

07:20.840 --> 07:23.229
What are you hearing
about the verdict?

07:23.270 --> 07:24.862
What?

07:24.910 --> 07:26.832
No.

07:26.880 --> 07:29.678
Are you serious? We are on
the verge of a race riot.

07:29.710 --> 07:31.871
And you're asking me about
the governor's sex life?!
Race riot?

07:31.910 --> 07:33.775
Really?
Shh.

07:33.820 --> 07:35.242
No, I will not
dignify that.

07:35.280 --> 07:37.248
Just call me again
when you get serious.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.246
Yep, black people.

07:39.290 --> 07:41.258
Just can't help
themselves, can they?

07:41.290 --> 07:42.621
I'm not saying
you'll riot.

07:42.660 --> 07:43.820
Oh, thanks.

07:43.860 --> 07:45.487
Well, you're not like other...

07:46.560 --> 07:47.788
...people.
What other people?

07:47.830 --> 07:49.149
Black people?
No.

07:49.200 --> 07:50.599
What, am I not
black enough?

07:50.630 --> 07:51.995
No... y-yes...

07:56.570 --> 07:58.231
You're more suburban.

07:58.270 --> 08:00.636
