08:23.630 --> 08:25.166
JOSH: You can't defer
to governor's office.

08:25.200 --> 08:26.736
That's like throwing
the "you know" to the sharks.

08:26.770 --> 08:28.533
I agree, but what
does she say?

08:28.570 --> 08:31.209
All marriages have their, uh,
their blah-blahs, their trials.

08:31.240 --> 08:33.572
That's acknowledging the
premise of the question.

08:33.610 --> 08:34.804
He slept with prostitutes.
I think the premise has
been acknowledged.

08:34.840 --> 08:36.899
"What_ does this have to do with
my job as state's attorney?"

08:36.950 --> 08:38.599
How is that not accepting
the premise of the question?

08:38.650 --> 08:39.617
Questioning
the question.

08:39.650 --> 08:41.174
Okay, guys, guys.

08:41.220 --> 08:43.040
I am gonna say it's
none of their business.

08:43.090 --> 08:45.046
JOSH: It is their business, and
that'll make you look defensive.

08:45.090 --> 08:47.285
Say Peter and you have
to trust each other.

08:47.320 --> 08:48.287
No, she'll look
like a doormat.

08:48.320 --> 08:49.287
Can you let me finish?
Uh-oh.

08:49.320 --> 08:50.287
What?
Dad just texted me.

08:50.330 --> 08:51.285
He can't get ahold of you.

08:51.330 --> 08:52.558
The last one we want to hear

08:52.600 --> 08:53.555
from right now is the governor.

08:53.600 --> 08:54.589
No, the jury is coming in.

08:54.630 --> 08:56.052
What, wait, what?

08:56.100 --> 08:58.091
MARISSA: The Cole Willis jury
is coming in right now.

08:59.940 --> 09:01.589
They just went out,
are you kidding me?

