09:05.610 --> 09:07.032
(cell phone buzzes)
Okay, if they find
the cops guilty...

09:07.080 --> 09:08.934
They're not gonna find
the cops guilty.

09:08.980 --> 09:10.902
Not after ten
minutes of blah-ing.

09:10.950 --> 09:13.214
If the verdict comes back
not gurlty, then we have
to make a comment.

09:13.250 --> 09:15.047
No, it's too early-- we don't
know where this is going yet.

09:15.080 --> 09:17.719
I'm not saying she has to come
out pro-cop or anti-cop...

09:17.750 --> 09:20.355
(Josh and Johnny talking
over each other)

09:20.390 --> 09:22.950
Shh.

09:24.230 --> 09:25.925
Guys, guys.

09:25.960 --> 09:27.325
Okay, thanks.

09:27.360 --> 09:28.896
Shh.

09:28.930 --> 09:30.329
MATTHEWS: Good evening,
and welcome to the debate

09:30.370 --> 09:32.326
for Cook County
State's Attorney,

09:32.370 --> 09:34.588
coming to you from the ballroom
of the Bonaventure Hotel.

09:34.640 --> 09:36.039
Remember, in terms
of the affair,

09:36.070 --> 09:36.707
the charges are
unsubstantiated.

09:36.740 --> 09:38.332
And you want
to handle it

09:38.370 --> 09:39.906
within the sanctity
of your marriage.

09:39.940 --> 09:41.305
And don't get provocative
with the jury verdict.

09:41.340 --> 09:43.046
That could go
either way.

09:43.080 --> 09:45.139
Don't be thrown by the countdown
clock--- it's, uh, digital.

09:45.180 --> 09:46.716
Blinks green when you
have ten seconds left.
Green? Why does it blink green?

09:46.750 --> 09:47.910
Why not red?
I don't know.

09:47.950 --> 09:49.372
To screw with us.

09:49.420 --> 09:50.944
Oh, and meet Prady halfway
across the stage

09:50.990 --> 09:52.617
to shake his hand.

09:52.660 --> 09:54.878
Your mic is live, so say,
"Good to see you, Frank."

09:54.920 --> 09:56.012
You got it?
What?

09:56.060 --> 09:57.084
You got it?

09:57.130 --> 09:59.382
"Good to see
you, Frank."

09:59.430 --> 10:01.955
MATTHEWS: And now I'd like
to introduce the two candidates,

10:02.000 --> 10:05.060
Alicia Florrick
and Frank Prady.

10:05.100 --> 10:07.762
JOSH: Good luck,
you'll be great.

10:10.110 --> 10:12.066
Good to see you again, Alicia.

10:12.110 --> 10:13.236
Good to see you, too, Frank.

10:18.910 --> 10:20.946
MATTHEWS: There are limits
on the applause later,

10:20.980 --> 10:25.041
but for now, why don't we
all give them a big hand?

10:25.090 --> 10:27.081
(applause)

10:52.410 --> 10:54.446
"Take thou away from me
the noise of thy songs,

10:54.480 --> 10:58.211
"for I will not hear
the melody of thy viols.

10:58.250 --> 11:01.879
"But let justice roll down
as waters

11:01.920 --> 11:04.855
and righteousness
as a mighty stream."

11:04.890 --> 11:06.892
Now, that's why we're here.

11:06.930 --> 11:09.797
Not for the sweet words
of flattery,

11:09.830 --> 11:13.266
but for justice, peace.

11:14.470 --> 11:16.062
You can't get ahold of him?

11:16.100 --> 11:17.738
What do you mean,
you can't get ahold of him?

11:17.770 --> 11:20.034
ELI:
The mayor is in New Hampshire.

11:20.080 --> 11:23.243
You're kidding.

11:23.280 --> 11:24.872
It's not a bad thing.

11:24.910 --> 11:27.049
Looks like rank selfishness
on his part.

11:27.080 --> 11:28.877
Yes, except we're trying to stop
a riot from happening here.

11:28.920 --> 11:31.218
...interrupt the debate...
All right, get me his
chief of staff.

11:31.250 --> 11:32.888
I have her on
hold right now.

11:32.920 --> 11:35.218
So what? He's taking
a run for president?

11:35.260 --> 11:36.727
Well...

11:36.760 --> 11:37.454
WOMAN:
Eli! Sorry to keep you waiting.

11:37.490 --> 11:39.128
This must be about the verdict.

11:39.160 --> 11:40.320
Yes. The governor is worried

11:40.360 --> 11:41.896
about the mayor
being indisposed.

11:41.930 --> 11:43.989
Okay, well, tell him
not to worry, Eli.

11:44.030 --> 11:46.169
The mayor and I have been on
the phone for the last hour.

11:46.200 --> 11:47.428
Really?
How'd he do that?

11:47.470 --> 11:49.290
I've been watching him
on a live feed

11:49.340 --> 11:51.331
at a fund-raiser in Concord.

11:51.370 --> 11:54.874
Are you and I gonna
have trouble tonight, Eli?

11:54.910 --> 11:56.400
Not unless this explodes on us.

11:56.440 --> 11:58.305
Okay, it won't explode.

11:58.350 --> 12:00.079
The mayor canceled
all furloughs,

12:00.120 --> 12:01.747
we have 800 extra officers
on the street,

12:01.780 --> 12:03.384
in riot gear, with tear gas.

12:03.420 --> 12:05.411
They're going full Ferguson
on this, sir.

12:05.450 --> 12:08.055
FRANNY:
Oh, come on, Eli, this is hardly
an equivalent situation.

12:08.090 --> 12:09.489
PETER:
Put me on with her.

12:09.520 --> 12:10.953
Hold on.

12:10.990 --> 12:12.218
PETER:
Hello, Franny.

12:12.260 --> 12:13.921
Listen to me.
Can you hear me?

12:13.960 --> 12:15.154
Uh, yes, Mr. Governor.
How are you this evening?

12:15.200 --> 12:16.895
PETER:
I'm fine.

12:16.930 --> 12:18.466
I'm at the interdenominational
conference downtown

12:18.500 --> 12:20.365
and I need you to get your ass
down here right now,

12:20.400 --> 12:23.062
or I'm gonna drag the mayor
through the mud.

12:23.110 --> 12:24.998
I'm sorry, I'm not sure
what mud you're talking about.

12:25.040 --> 12:27.508
You know damn well
what mud I'm talking about.

12:27.540 --> 12:30.145
Now, I gave the mayor
early warning on this verdict,

12:30.180 --> 12:32.842
and he's still sitting
on his ass in New Hampshire,

12:32.880 --> 12:34.370
thinking he can sit this out
and blame me.

12:34.420 --> 12:35.819
Well, you can tell him

12:35.850 --> 12:37.112
that I'm the one in front

12:37.150 --> 12:38.412
of the cameras
with the megaphone.

12:38.450 --> 12:39.485
You have to understand,

12:39.520 --> 12:40.487
there were no flights,
so it's...

12:40.520 --> 12:42.283
(call cuts off)

12:42.320 --> 12:45.118
Wow.
All right, let's go.

12:45.160 --> 12:47.025
MATTHEWS:
Questions will be asked
of both candidates

12:47.060 --> 12:48.823
on a rotating basis,

12:48.860 --> 12:51.420
with the first candidate
given 45 seconds to respond,

12:51.470 --> 12:53.938
the second candidate,
30 seconds of rebuttal.

12:53.970 --> 12:57.098
If that rebuttal mentions
the other candidate by name,

12:57.140 --> 13:00.234
that candidate will have
20 seconds to respond.

13:00.280 --> 13:03.044
Both candidates will also have
ten seconds to ask the other

13:03.080 --> 13:04.377
a direct question.

13:04.410 --> 13:06.002
Unless, of course,

13:06.050 --> 13:09.542
the candidate has exceeded
his or her time,

13:09.580 --> 13:11.081
and then, that candidate
will have the option

13:11.120 --> 13:13.486
of adding to their time,
but only by subtracting it

13:13.520 --> 13:16.284
from their closing arguments.

13:16.320 --> 13:18.379
There will also be a lightning
round in which both candidates

13:18.430 --> 13:19.556
will have ten seconds
to respond.

13:19.590 --> 13:21.091
Mr. Prady, you have 15 seconds.

13:21.130 --> 13:23.189
PRADY:
I come in with a clean slate.

13:23.230 --> 13:25.494
I have no
bureaucratic grudges.

13:25.530 --> 13:27.259
Nothing to prove.

13:27.300 --> 13:28.528
All I see

13:28.570 --> 13:30.231
is a city that
needs a new way,

13:30.270 --> 13:32.067
and I want to
be that new way.

13:32.110 --> 13:33.805
MATTHEWS:
Mrs. Florrick.

13:37.350 --> 13:39.306
I hear that a lot.

13:39.350 --> 13:42.569
A new way, a new approach
to crime on our streets.

13:42.620 --> 13:43.985
But no matter what,

13:44.020 --> 13:45.612
whenever I vote
for that person,

13:45.650 --> 13:48.289
we end up
right where we started.

13:48.320 --> 13:50.424
We end up with...

13:50.460 --> 13:54.624
um, uh, the murder rate
continually climbing.

13:54.660 --> 13:56.969
We end up...

13:57.000 --> 13:58.592
In short, inexperience is not a
value. It is something to be...

13:58.630 --> 14:00.063
MATTHEWS:
Mrs. Florrick, your time is up.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.965
Mr. Prady, in about ten minutes

14:02.000 --> 14:03.433
we'll have a verdict in the
Cole WIIIIS manslaughter case.

14:03.470 --> 14:05.358
Do you have a comment
on that trial?

14:05.410 --> 14:07.901
PRADY:
Well, Chris, uh, I will
in about ten minutes.

14:07.940 --> 14:09.601
For now, all I can say
is I think we have

14:09.640 --> 14:11.540
to take a look
at police traInIng.

14:11.580 --> 14:13.218
ELI:
Why is she frowning?

14:13.250 --> 14:14.911
You have her frowning.
Well, this is all new to her.

14:14.950 --> 14:16.884
Give her a second.
No, you prepped her wrong.

14:16.920 --> 14:18.547
You got... I got to go.

14:18.590 --> 14:20.979
Yeah, Eli, I just got off
the phone with the mayor.

14:21.020 --> 14:22.487
We're not gonna leave
the police exposed.

14:22.520 --> 14:23.487
No one said they'll be exposed.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.929
But they go in with riot gear,

14:24.960 --> 14:26.359
they'll create a riot.

14:26.390 --> 14:27.618
That's what happened
in Ferguson.

14:27.660 --> 14:29.457
Okay, but with all due
respect to the governor,

14:29.500 --> 14:31.161
we're deferring to
the police on this.

14:31.200 --> 14:32.497
No, no, no.
You're playing politics

14:34.700 --> 14:36.634
Okay, and you want the
African-American support, sir.

14:36.670 --> 14:39.161
No one's winning
a Nobel Peace Prize here.

14:39.210 --> 14:40.507
No one wins if there's a riot.
Pastor!

14:40.540 --> 14:41.632
Come on, let's not play

14:41.680 --> 14:43.443
dueling pastors here.
Pastor Jeremiah,

14:43.480 --> 14:45.175
I believe you know
the mayor's chief of staff.

14:45.210 --> 14:46.438
Yes, I do. Good evening.

14:46.480 --> 14:48.175
Good evening.
She believes the police

14:48.220 --> 14:49.573
should be ready
with riot gear and tear gas.

14:49.620 --> 14:51.383
Uh, that would be
a terrible mistake.

14:51.420 --> 14:53.081
I mean, the people want
to see justice done,

14:53.120 --> 14:54.553
but they will protest

14:54.590 --> 14:56.512
peaceably unless
they are provoked.

14:56.560 --> 14:57.356
ELI:
Franny?

14:57.390 --> 14:58.687
The mayor goes in
like storm troopers,

14:58.730 --> 15:00.652
he'll be blamed.

15:00.700 --> 15:02.497
PRADY:
That attitude is contagious.

15:02.530 --> 15:04.623
It diffuses a situation.

15:04.670 --> 15:06.194
And it's all cyclical.

15:06.230 --> 15:08.369
How's she doing?
I can't tell.

15:08.400 --> 15:10.459
There's some bad
body language there.
Take a look at police training.

15:10.510 --> 15:12.034
MATTHEWS:
And your time is up, Mr. Prady.

15:12.070 --> 15:13.503
Lightning round.

15:13.540 --> 15:14.575
Do you believe the police
were at fault

15:14.610 --> 15:16.168
in Ferguson, Mrs. Florrick?

15:16.210 --> 15:17.199
(clears her throat)

15:17.250 --> 15:19.206
Well, I'm not sure...

15:19.250 --> 15:20.376
Actually, it's
the lightning round.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.614
You only have five seconds.

15:22.650 --> 15:24.948
It's complicated.

15:24.990 --> 15:26.639
Mr. Prady?
It's a systemic problem.

15:26.690 --> 15:29.011
Good. Next question.
Talk to us about

15:29.060 --> 15:30.982
race relations in Chicago,
Mrs. Florrick.

15:31.030 --> 15:33.624
You've got 45 seconds.

15:33.660 --> 15:36.220
(knocks)
Hi.
It's, uh, a work in progress.

15:36.260 --> 15:37.329
You found out
something about Evan?

15:37.370 --> 15:39.167
He's working with David Lee?

15:39.200 --> 15:41.532
No.
Then why is he caving?

15:41.570 --> 15:44.539
His son was undergoing surgery
to remove histiocytosis tumors

15:44.570 --> 15:46.970
at the Lurie
Children's Hospital today.

15:47.010 --> 15:48.568
Did you know that?
No.

15:48.610 --> 15:50.168
The operation was successful.

15:50.210 --> 15:51.973
He just found out an hour ago.

15:52.010 --> 15:53.568
Well, I'm glad.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.315
_ But_...
Yes, It was just before

15:55.350 --> 15:57.409
he made the $30 million
settlement offer.

15:57.450 --> 15:59.179
He's become nice.

15:59.220 --> 16:00.653
CARY:
Uh-oh. We should send him home.

16:00.690 --> 16:02.055
DIANE:
No.

16:02.090 --> 16:03.626
We could open ourselves
to a malpractice suit

16:03.660 --> 16:04.752
from Neil Gross.

16:04.790 --> 16:06.485
CARY:
Then, we step in.

16:06.530 --> 16:07.622
DIANE:
Yes.

16:07.660 --> 16:09.548
Supply the backbone.
Kalinda, did you

16:09.600 --> 16:11.693
do any background work
on Mrs. Gross

16:11.730 --> 16:13.664
before their marriage?
Yes.

16:13.700 --> 16:15.338
And afterwards.

16:15.370 --> 16:18.100
Freelance work for David Lee?
Yes.

16:18.140 --> 16:19.562
He wanted to see
if she was cheating on him.

16:19.610 --> 16:23.046
Is there anything
interesting there?

16:24.180 --> 16:26.102
Yes.

16:26.150 --> 16:27.344
Photos.

16:28.620 --> 16:31.111
Good. Poetic justice.

16:31.150 --> 16:33.584
Using David Lee's work
against him.

16:33.620 --> 16:35.156
(applause on television)

16:35.190 --> 16:36.259
MATTHEWS:
Mrs. Florrick?

16:36.290 --> 16:38.178
You have ten seconds to respond.

16:38.230 --> 16:39.481
Uh, crime is crime.

16:39.530 --> 16:41.293
Black and white
shouldn't matter.

16:41.330 --> 16:44.322
It often does,
but that shouldn't prevent

16:44.370 --> 16:45.598
the state's attorney from...
Your time is up.

16:45.630 --> 16:46.597
But why don't you

16:46.630 --> 16:48.530
finish that sentence?

16:48.570 --> 16:50.629
...doing my job.

16:50.670 --> 16:51.807
Good. Now, let's turn
to our journalists.

16:51.840 --> 16:53.330
First up, Patrick Mancini

16:53.380 --> 16:54.631
from The Middeleton Herald.

16:54.680 --> 16:55.635
Do you have a question?

16:55.680 --> 16:57.147
I do. Thank you.

16:57.180 --> 16:59.705
Mrs. Florrick,
your husband has not

16:59.750 --> 17:01.775
always been faithful
to you in your marriage.

17:01.820 --> 17:03.811
In 2009 he, in
fact, resigned from

17:03.850 --> 17:06.648
the office you're now seeking
partly because he was caught

17:06.690 --> 17:08.555
in a sexual scandal...
I'm gonna Interrupt you
right there, Mr. Mancini.

17:08.590 --> 17:10.729
Actually,
I'm not finished, ma'am.
Yes.

17:10.760 --> 17:12.387
But you already called
my campaign manager

17:12.430 --> 17:14.398
with your question,
so I'm going

17:14.430 --> 17:15.590
to save you the trouble.
Oh, my God.

17:15.630 --> 17:17.188
What is she doing?
You have photos

17:17.230 --> 17:19.391
of my husband supposedly
at the apartment

17:19.430 --> 17:20.738
of his legal counsel--
is that correct?

17:20.770 --> 17:22.192
I wish you'd just let me
answer my question,

17:22.240 --> 17:23.605
Mrs. Florrick... _
I mean, ask my question,

17:23.640 --> 17:25.369
Mrs. Florrick... _
My daughter is In the audience

17:25.410 --> 17:27.799
tonight, sir,
and I would like to do her

17:27.840 --> 17:29.728
the favor of addressing your
question, not answering it.

17:29.780 --> 17:31.475
Holy...
Ow, stop!

17:31.510 --> 17:32.807
This is how

17:32.850 --> 17:33.748
I would answer your question,

17:33.780 --> 17:36.248
Mr. Mancini.

17:36.280 --> 17:37.713
How dare you, sir?

17:37.750 --> 17:39.411
Do you have
a personal life?

17:39.450 --> 17:41.486
Do you have a spouse?

17:41.520 --> 17:42.851
Do you know
what it would be like

17:42.890 --> 17:45.654
to have
your personal life spilled

17:45.690 --> 17:47.123
across the stage like this?

17:47.160 --> 17:48.593
Broadcasted

17:48.630 --> 17:50.393
into the homes of your friends,
your workmates,

17:50.430 --> 17:52.762
your daughter's
friends at school?

17:52.800 --> 17:54.336
Do you know
what that would be like?
Ma'am, I'm only reporting...

17:54.370 --> 17:55.689
It would be one thing if my job

17:55.740 --> 17:57.731
had anything to do with
my husband's infidelity.

17:57.770 --> 17:59.806
I'm not even sure
what job that would be.

17:59.840 --> 18:02.729
But your question would
at least then be pertinent.

18:02.780 --> 18:04.668
But I'm running
for state's attorney.

18:04.710 --> 18:06.871
I am running
to be someone to put

18:06.910 --> 18:08.844
a dent in crime in this town.

18:08.880 --> 18:11.519
What does that have to do
with my married life?

18:11.550 --> 18:13.757
That was terrific.

18:13.790 --> 18:16.679
Uh-oh. She's brought
her own pastor.

18:16.720 --> 18:20.429
ALICIA: ...about my husband's
alleged infidelity would.

18:20.460 --> 18:22.257
All right, I'll deal with that.

18:22.300 --> 18:24.723
Why don't you make sure
the police don't overreact?

18:24.770 --> 18:26.726
ALICIA:
Because it's the only story...
This is gonna be fine.

18:26.770 --> 18:28.567
Gonna be fine.
MATTHEWS:
Actually, Mrs. Florrick...

18:28.600 --> 18:29.862
I know that I am past my time.

18:29.900 --> 18:31.208
But let me just finish up.

18:31.240 --> 18:33.435
We are real people up here.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.175
Mr. Prady and myself.

18:35.210 --> 18:36.575
We're not cartoons.

18:36.610 --> 18:39.704
When you hurt us,
we actually do bleed.

18:39.750 --> 18:41.718
I know that that is hard
for you to remember,

18:41.750 --> 18:44.514
Mr. Mancini,
but it is worth trying.

18:44.550 --> 18:47.383
If not for me,
then for my daughter.

18:47.420 --> 18:49.581
I, um...

18:49.620 --> 18:51.520
Yes, thank you. Mr. Prady?

18:51.560 --> 18:53.255
Do you have a response?
I never finished my question.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.791
MATTHEWS:
Sure, if you want
to finish your question.

18:55.830 --> 18:57.889
MANCINI:
I'm breaking a story tomorrow

18:57.930 --> 18:59.363
about the governor sleeping
with his legal counsel.

18:59.400 --> 19:00.662
(crowd booing)

19:00.700 --> 19:01.792
I didn't create the story.

19:01.840 --> 19:02.761
I'm just reporting on it.

19:02.800 --> 19:03.801
Why don't I turn to Frank Prady?

19:03.840 --> 19:05.705
Uh, 15 seconds.

19:05.740 --> 19:06.809
Do you have a rebuttal?

19:06.840 --> 19:07.829
Uh, I don't have a rebuttal, no.

19:07.880 --> 19:09.438
But I, uh, I will say this.

19:09.480 --> 19:12.278
I think Mrs. Florrick
deserves an apology

19:12.310 --> 19:13.868
from the press.
(crowd cheering)

19:18.590 --> 19:20.808
Ah, my own handiwork.

19:20.860 --> 19:22.657
What are you talking about?

19:22.690 --> 19:24.328
David had you followed when he
was representing your spouse.

19:24.360 --> 19:25.622
That's why your prenup is void.

19:25.660 --> 19:26.649
Isn't that right, Evan?

19:26.690 --> 19:28.794
Yes, it is.

19:28.830 --> 19:30.388
David,

19:30.430 --> 19:32.295
$15 million is as high as we go.

19:32.330 --> 19:34.730
No. I'll keep these.

19:34.770 --> 19:36.897
We have the originals, David.

19:36.940 --> 19:38.407
Good. Keep them.

19:38.440 --> 19:40.476
These are good enough for TMZ.

19:40.510 --> 19:42.330
Not that I'll give it to them.
I'm not sure you're getting

19:42.380 --> 19:44.678
this, David-- your
client broke her vows.
Yes.

19:44.710 --> 19:46.678
By sleeping with Mr. Gross'
biggest competitor.

19:46.710 --> 19:48.814
That'll look good for you,
won't it, Mr. Gross?

19:48.850 --> 19:51.512
Your wife prefers
SleuthWay over Chumhum?
Amazing.

19:51.550 --> 19:53.552
Just amazing.

19:53.590 --> 19:56.309
Half my life is about
lawyers these days, and just

19:56.360 --> 19:57.918
when I think
I have reached bottom,

19:57.960 --> 19:59.427
the ninth circle of hell,

19:59.460 --> 20:02.258
there is always a circle lower.

20:04.930 --> 20:06.522
(door opens)

20:06.570 --> 20:07.969
(door closes)

20:08.000 --> 20:09.865
After he calms down,

20:09.900 --> 20:11.868
tell him we'll settle
for $100 million.

20:11.910 --> 20:15.676
You have three hours
or we're out of here.

20:15.710 --> 20:16.699
Governor Florrick.

20:16.740 --> 20:18.776
Pastor.

20:18.810 --> 20:20.971
Hello, Father.

20:21.020 --> 20:23.238
Son.

20:23.290 --> 20:24.917
FRANNY:
Mr. Governor,
Pastor Isaiah believes

20:24.950 --> 20:26.542
the mayor's plan

20:26.590 --> 20:28.387
is the best way to handle
any possible violence.

20:28.420 --> 20:29.318
Really?

20:29.360 --> 20:30.759
Is that what you believe?

20:30.790 --> 20:32.826
I just know about
a deal between you

20:32.860 --> 20:35.522
and my father.
(stammers)
What deal?

20:35.560 --> 20:39.428
An $80,000 religious study?

20:39.470 --> 20:40.960
And I think it will be
evident to those upset

20:41.000 --> 20:43.309
by the verdict
that they're being misled.

20:43.340 --> 20:44.364
Why do you hate me so much, son?

20:44.410 --> 20:45.968
I don't hate you, Father.

20:46.010 --> 20:48.535
I just believe you're
being misled by politics.

20:48.580 --> 20:50.775
It's your mother, isn't it?
She put you up to this.

20:50.810 --> 20:52.448
Okay, the mayor's plan has been
implemented, Mr. Governor.

20:52.480 --> 20:53.777
He asks that you assist
in his efforts

20:53.820 --> 20:55.811
by not withholding
the National Guard reserves.

20:55.850 --> 20:57.317
Well, this isn't good.

20:57.350 --> 20:59.443
The verdict is in.
Oh, crap.

20:59.490 --> 21:01.913
I'm calling the mayor.
Get out the National Guard.

21:01.960 --> 21:04.724
Franny, if the mayor goes in
with this warrior stance,

21:04.760 --> 21:06.352
there's going to be violence.
MATTHEWS:
Mr. Prady?

21:06.390 --> 21:08.927
The point is, drug arrests
have been on the rise

21:08.960 --> 21:11.064
for years now and the sentencing
guidelines are crazily wrong.

21:11.100 --> 21:12.169
I'm sorry.
Time's up, Mr. Prady.

21:12.200 --> 21:14.760
Mrs. Florrick, you have
ten seconds for a rebuttal.

21:14.800 --> 21:17.360
Yes, well, talking
about guidelines,

21:17.410 --> 21:18.729
if there were guidelines
that we...

21:18.770 --> 21:19.839
I'm sorry again.
One second.

21:19.870 --> 21:21.679
Excuse me.

21:21.710 --> 21:23.598
(indistinct chatter)

21:23.650 --> 21:26.744
Our live feed
has been interrupted.

21:26.780 --> 21:28.042
Uh, what the hell?
Damn it.

21:28.080 --> 21:29.547
She was just getting
into a rhythm.

21:29.580 --> 21:31.582
We're being asked
to take a pause here.

21:31.620 --> 21:34.953
The Cole Willis verdict is in.

21:34.990 --> 21:37.424
And we're switching over
to live coverage.

21:37.460 --> 21:39.781
Uh, the hope is that in one
or two hours, they'll switch

21:39.830 --> 21:41.627
back to the debate.

21:41.660 --> 21:43.924
Stay tuned.

21:43.970 --> 21:45.767
Great job. You're kicking ass.

21:45.800 --> 21:47.461
Way to neutralize the sex stuff.

21:47.500 --> 21:48.637
Do you want some water?
No, where's the food?

21:48.670 --> 21:49.864
I'm starving.
In the hotel kitchen.

21:49.900 --> 21:52.505
You want me to make you a plate?

21:54.610 --> 21:56.976
You're doing great, Mom.

22:00.420 --> 22:02.877
The verdict is in,
and the two police officers

22:02.920 --> 22:05.809
who killed suspected gang member
Cole Willis

22:05.850 --> 22:08.353
during a routine arrest
were found innocent

22:08.390 --> 22:09.550
of all charges.

22:09.590 --> 22:10.887
Suspected gang member.

22:10.930 --> 22:12.557
Really? The suburban
father of two?

22:12.590 --> 22:14.490
Okay, let's not get upset.

22:14.530 --> 22:16.122
Why? You afraid
I'm gonna riot?

22:16.160 --> 22:17.491
Nora.

22:17.530 --> 22:19.395
This is your
Giuliani moment, sir.

22:19.430 --> 22:20.692
Careers are built
on moments like...

22:20.740 --> 22:22.958
Eli.
I'm not saying you take
advantage of it,

22:23.000 --> 22:24.558
but no one will talk
about Ramona

22:24.610 --> 22:26.737
if you handle this properly.
Eli, you need to stop.

22:38.450 --> 22:40.042
(door opens)

22:40.090 --> 22:42.012
PRADY: Oh, good,
I'm starved.

22:42.060 --> 22:43.925
(chuckles) Did they tell you
not to eat, too?

22:43.960 --> 22:45.427
Yes.

22:45.460 --> 22:47.428
So, how do you think
it's going?

22:47.460 --> 22:50.429
Oh, I don't know.

22:50.470 --> 22:52.688
Every time I get started,
they say, "Time's up."

22:52.730 --> 22:54.766
You had a good answer
to that one reporter.

22:54.800 --> 22:57.166
You were good
with the racial question.

22:57.200 --> 22:59.509
It's all artificial, isn't it?

23:00.710 --> 23:02.507
We agree on more
than we don't.

23:02.540 --> 23:04.679
(chuckles)

23:04.710 --> 23:06.177
We should debate now.

23:06.210 --> 23:09.509
See if we disagree
on anything.

23:11.520 --> 23:13.715
Our handlers won't be happy.

23:18.190 --> 23:19.828
Okay, you start.

23:30.840 --> 23:32.865
ALICIA: It helps no one
to throw the baby out

23:32.910 --> 23:33.831
with the bath water.

23:33.880 --> 23:36.474
The system need to be tweaked,
not overhauled.

23:36.510 --> 23:37.704
You really believe that?

23:37.750 --> 23:39.047
I do.

23:39.080 --> 23:40.843
We're on the verge
of another Ferguson...

23:40.880 --> 23:43.713
No, no, no, that was just
about jury selection.

23:43.750 --> 23:45.547
The prosecution screwed up
on voir dire.

23:45.590 --> 23:47.182
That's why those two cops
were found not guilty.

23:47.220 --> 23:48.858
No, they were found not guilty
because the system

23:48.890 --> 23:51.222
is inherently racist.
Ask anyone.

23:51.260 --> 23:53.899
So what do you do then?
If the system is racist,

23:53.930 --> 23:55.852
what is the state's attorney
supposed...?
You start with hiring.

23:55.900 --> 23:58.664
The racial diversity
in the office is a joke.

23:58.700 --> 24:01.760
How many white prosecutors...
No, but the exact opposite
needs to be done.

24:01.800 --> 24:03.609
It needs_to be
a pure meritocracy.

24:03.640 --> 24:05.198
No cronyism.
To consider race?

24:05.240 --> 24:06.730
That's not cronyism.

24:06.770 --> 24:08.499
Yes, it is.

24:08.540 --> 24:10.770
We need good prosecutors.

24:10.810 --> 24:13.199
There are a dozen
defense attorneys I know

24:13.250 --> 24:14.877
making $400,000 a year

24:14.920 --> 24:17.946
that would jump at the chance
to put criminals away.

24:17.990 --> 24:19.981
They're sick of what
they're doing now and...

24:20.020 --> 24:21.885
W-Why don't they?

24:21.920 --> 24:23.626
What?
You said they'd jump

24:23.660 --> 24:24.922
at the chance
to be a prosecutor.

24:24.960 --> 24:25.927
Well, what's stopping them?

24:25.960 --> 24:27.825
Well, what's stopping them

24:27.860 --> 24:29.259
is_that the office
is poorly run.

24:29.300 --> 24:30.790
They know they're gonna spend
half their time

24:30.830 --> 24:31.990
dealing with
a stupid bureaucracy.

24:32.030 --> 24:33.930
No, no, they don't jump

24:33.970 --> 24:35.631
because it's easier to talk

24:35.670 --> 24:37.535
about doing good than it is
to actually do good.

24:37.570 --> 24:40.164
(laughs)
And you call me cynical?

24:40.210 --> 24:42.531
Chicago is on the verge
of another Ferguson,

24:42.580 --> 24:44.639
because the system is all white.

24:44.680 --> 24:46.978
Because African-Americans
don't see someone

24:47.010 --> 24:48.546
who shares their experience.

24:48.580 --> 24:49.911
MAN:
You know what's really stupid?

24:49.950 --> 24:51.986
You're two white people arguing

24:52.020 --> 24:53.783
about why black people
are rioting.

24:53.820 --> 24:55.685
That's what's stupid.

24:55.720 --> 24:57.859
And you're saying there needs to
be more black people in office,

24:57.890 --> 25:00.893
and that's why we need
two more white people running.

25:02.900 --> 25:04.891
Okay.

25:05.900 --> 25:07.697
So what do you do?

25:07.740 --> 25:09.890
Stop prosecuting
so many drug crimes.

25:09.940 --> 25:11.532
That's exactly my plan
for office.
Exactly!

25:11.570 --> 25:12.901
That's why you
should vote for me.

25:12.940 --> 25:14.168
They put a guy in prison

25:14.210 --> 25:16.098
for killing a dog
just last week.

25:16.140 --> 25:17.949
Then these two cops kill
a black man,

25:17.980 --> 25:19.277
and what happens?

25:19.310 --> 25:21.175
They go free?
We should go there.

25:21.220 --> 25:23.245
Now.
What?

25:23.280 --> 25:24.747
Pastor Isaiah, would you like
to come with me?

25:24.790 --> 25:26.610
Where you going?

25:26.650 --> 25:28.015
There._
...to express their outrage

25:28.060 --> 25:29.209
over the innocent verdict...

25:29.260 --> 25:30.887
Are you serious?

25:30.930 --> 25:32.181
Yes.

25:32.230 --> 25:34.892
Yes, let's go.

25:34.930 --> 25:36.795
...where hundreds
of people protesting

25:36.830 --> 25:38.889
the Cole Willis verdict
have begun gathering

25:38.930 --> 25:40.932
outside the city courthouse.

25:40.970 --> 25:42.961
I'm gonna have trouble
getting home tonight.
You might as well

25:43.000 --> 25:44.206
start home now.

25:44.240 --> 25:45.867
You want these photos on TMZ?
We do.

25:45.910 --> 25:48.606
I don't bluff, Diane.
You know I don't.

25:48.640 --> 25:50.949
I don't, either.
What's this?

25:50.980 --> 25:53.244
Deena's employment contract
as in-house counsel

25:53.280 --> 25:55.077
at Chumhum.
Evan, what's going on?

25:55.120 --> 25:56.678
There's a standard
non-compete clause

25:56.720 --> 25:59.587
in the contracts.
Oh, come on.

25:59.620 --> 26:01.850
DIANE: Deena was sleeping
with the CEO of Chumhum's

26:01.890 --> 26:04.358
greatest competitor during
the time of that contract.

26:04.390 --> 26:07.154
If you ask me, that violates
her non-compete.

26:07.190 --> 26:08.896
That opens her up to a suit.

26:08.930 --> 26:10.898
God, you guys are terrible.

26:10.930 --> 26:12.591
Evan, do you agree

26:12.630 --> 26:13.961
with these kind of tactics?

26:14.000 --> 26:15.831
I'm sorry, David.

26:15.870 --> 26:17.599
Yes, we're all sorry.

26:17.640 --> 26:19.130
$15 million.

26:19.170 --> 26:22.879
You have an hour to accept
or it goes away.

26:22.910 --> 26:24.172
ALICIA:
My law partner, Cary Agos,

26:24.210 --> 26:26.599
was prosecuted on trumped-up
drug charges,

26:26.650 --> 26:27.844
so I understand this issue.

26:27.880 --> 26:29.211
Yeah, and he had
all the advantages

26:29.250 --> 26:31.343
of a white
entitled businessman.

26:31.390 --> 26:33.881
He's a lawyer, he knew lavwers,

26:33.920 --> 26:35.717
and he knew
how to work the system,

26:35.760 --> 26:37.057
but you take any
African-American up

26:37.090 --> 26:38.352
on drug charges...
Alicia. Here you are.

26:38.390 --> 26:40.187
Why don't we head back
to the greenroom?

26:40.230 --> 26:41.390
No, I'll meet you there.
No, I think

26:41.430 --> 26:43.193
we should go together.
Hey, let them talk.

26:43.230 --> 26:45.721
She said she'd
see you later. So what?

26:45.770 --> 26:47.635
You would just stop
prosecuting all drug crime?

26:47.670 --> 26:49.399
No, nonviolent drug crimes.

26:49.440 --> 26:50.964
I would de-emphasize them.

26:51.010 --> 26:52.329
You can just do that?
I can,

26:52.370 --> 26:53.632
but I'm not sure Alicia can.

26:53.680 --> 26:54.635
Why is that?

26:54.680 --> 26:56.079
Politics.

26:56.110 --> 26:57.407
I believe she'd want

26:57.440 --> 26:59.078
to de-emphasize drug crimes,

26:59.110 --> 27:00.714
but her critics would suggest

27:00.750 --> 27:02.843
she was doing this
as a favor to her old client,

27:02.880 --> 27:04.108
Lemond Bishop,

27:04.150 --> 27:05.082
a top drug dealer.

27:05.120 --> 27:06.246
And they would be wrong.

27:06.290 --> 27:07.882
Which wouldn't matter.

27:07.920 --> 27:09.785
The politics would
work against her

27:09.820 --> 27:11.287
relaxing drug prosecutions.

27:11.330 --> 27:12.957
But I don't have
any history here.

27:12.990 --> 27:15.788
I am free and clear to act.

27:15.830 --> 27:17.422
Okay, folks,
I think we're done here.

27:17.460 --> 27:19.667
Why would you want to stop
prosecuting drug crimes?
I can barely

27:19.700 --> 27:21.861
walk home at night with all
the dealers on my street.

27:21.900 --> 27:23.663
'Cause it's mostly
putting blacks in prison.

27:23.710 --> 27:25.359
Yeah, well, maybe they
should be in prison.

27:25.410 --> 27:27.332
Excuse me, why is this
all about black people?

27:27.370 --> 27:29.031
Most of the trouble
I have in my neighborhood

27:29.080 --> 27:30.672
is because of the blacks.

27:30.710 --> 27:32.109
Okay, wait, wait, what?

27:32.150 --> 27:33.344
I'm just telling you what
happens in my neighborhood.

27:33.380 --> 27:34.677
No, you're spouting

27:34.720 --> 27:35.914
racist bull.
That's not

27:35.950 --> 27:37.019
what I'm doing.
Actually, you know what, man?

27:37.050 --> 27:38.745
there's no taping in here.

27:38.790 --> 27:40.212
Uh, it's a proprietary issue
with the hotel.

27:40.250 --> 27:43.686
(sirens wailing)

27:47.260 --> 27:49.296
How have you been, Pastor?

27:49.330 --> 27:52.128
I'm well.

27:52.170 --> 27:54.195
I see that you have been, too.

27:54.240 --> 27:56.231
I have.

27:58.110 --> 28:00.237
It's been a while.

28:00.270 --> 28:02.135
It has.

28:02.180 --> 28:03.238
How are you and Alicia?

28:04.450 --> 28:06.338
Fine.

28:07.780 --> 28:08.769
No.

28:08.820 --> 28:11.983
No, you haven't been.

28:12.020 --> 28:15.114
Well, life's...

28:15.160 --> 28:17.151
complicated.
(scoffs)

28:17.190 --> 28:19.181
It is.

28:20.160 --> 28:22.128
Still believe?

28:24.800 --> 28:26.199
Do I believe in God?

28:28.340 --> 28:30.331
At times.

28:31.540 --> 28:33.132
You still pray?

28:35.840 --> 28:37.842
No.

28:40.210 --> 28:42.474
Do you want me to pray for you?

28:42.520 --> 28:46.513
I don't know what
I'd have you pray for.

28:46.550 --> 28:49.155
That you be a good man.

28:50.160 --> 28:52.151
Do you want to be good?

28:55.200 --> 28:58.795
I think it's
a little late for that.

28:58.830 --> 29:01.936
I want to be...

29:01.970 --> 29:03.961
effective.

29:05.140 --> 29:07.779
Does one discount the other?

29:07.810 --> 29:10.529
It can.

29:10.580 --> 29:12.775
Tonight, for example...

29:15.080 --> 29:17.787
...I need to be effective.

29:21.290 --> 29:23.315
Pray for that.

29:24.930 --> 29:26.079
Okay, then what do you do?

29:26.130 --> 29:28.098
You talk about equality,

29:28.130 --> 29:29.290
you talk
about overcoming racism.

29:30.560 --> 29:32.266
No, that's the poetry.

29:32.300 --> 29:34.291
That makes people feel good
when you say it, but that is not

29:34.340 --> 29:36.991
the S.A.'s job, and it wouldn't
make a bit of a difference.

29:37.040 --> 29:38.234
That's cynicism talking.

29:38.270 --> 29:40.261
No, that's a defense attorney
talking,

29:40.310 --> 29:44.007
saying that I have
seen firsthand what
prosecutors do wrong.

29:44.050 --> 29:45.142
And I know how to correct it.

29:45.180 --> 29:46.579
That's why I'll be
better at it than you.

29:46.610 --> 29:48.146
You're not... _
Because I'm not trying

29:48.180 --> 29:49.147
to remake the world.

29:49.180 --> 29:51.284
I don't think
I can change people.

29:51.320 --> 29:53.140
I think I can
change the office.

29:53.190 --> 29:55.158
You know what, go ahead
and shoot whatever you want.

29:55.190 --> 29:57.078
I can put defense
attorneys in office

29:57.120 --> 29:58.485
who are hungry to
put criminals away.

29:58.530 --> 30:02.159
I can go after the top crooks
because I know who they are.

30:02.200 --> 30:03.121
Because you represented them.

30:03.160 --> 30:04.297
Yes!

30:04.330 --> 30:06.298
And I know how they work.

30:06.330 --> 30:08.139
I'm not going in, hoping
for pie in the sky.

30:08.170 --> 30:10.035
We've had enough pretty words.

30:10.070 --> 30:12.459
We've had enough of novices
who talk a good game

30:12.510 --> 30:14.933
but then throw their hands up
when they realize

30:14.980 --> 30:16.129
they can't stop racism.

30:16.180 --> 30:18.000
They can't make everyone good.

30:18.050 --> 30:20.143
That's why people
should vote for me and not you.

30:20.180 --> 30:21.477
(applause)

30:23.650 --> 30:25.584
Frank!

30:25.620 --> 30:27.349
Let's go.

30:27.390 --> 30:28.459
Now. You're eight points up.

30:28.490 --> 30:29.855
Don't squander it.

30:29.890 --> 30:31.027
Oh.
We can get a photo.

30:31.060 --> 30:32.084
Ready? One, two, three.

30:38.230 --> 30:41.597
A black man who did everything
he was supposed to do.

30:41.640 --> 30:43.392
He went to the hospital.
What did they do?

30:43.440 --> 30:45.362
They sent him home
with some aspirin.

30:45.410 --> 30:47.162
Everybody white got cured.

30:47.210 --> 30:50.008
Just the black guy they
sent home with some pills.

30:50.040 --> 30:52.406
(protesters singing)
(siren chirps)

30:52.450 --> 30:53.405
Let's go.

30:53.450 --> 30:55.418
(indistinct shouting)

31:03.420 --> 31:04.978
George, how are you?

31:05.030 --> 31:06.383
So you lucked out, Eli.
What are you talking about?

31:06.430 --> 31:07.897
The governor is sleeping
with his lawyer,

31:07.930 --> 31:09.420
and what's the_ headline?
A race not?

31:09.460 --> 31:11.098
How dare you, George?
The governor is facing

31:11.130 --> 31:12.222
one of the biggest challenges
of his life.

31:12.270 --> 31:13.259
Am I quoting you now?

31:13.300 --> 31:14.392
No, just background.

31:14.440 --> 31:15.896
And you're obsessing

31:15.940 --> 31:17.430
about some stupid,
unsubstantiated sideshow?

31:17.470 --> 31:19.267
Okay, okay, so what do you
want me to quote?

31:19.310 --> 31:22.074
Well, the governor is pulling
up right now. I want you to...

31:22.110 --> 31:24.101
...to look over there

31:24.150 --> 31:26.243
and I will bring
the governor to you.
Why? What's going on?

31:26.280 --> 31:27.474
Do you want access, George?

31:27.510 --> 31:29.046
Then go over there.

31:31.620 --> 31:33.383
What are you doing here?

31:33.420 --> 31:34.409
Are you insane?

31:34.460 --> 31:36.212
The governor asked for me.

31:36.260 --> 31:38.285
Have you seen the news?
No one's reporting it.

31:38.330 --> 31:40.423
Because I've been killing
myself trying to keep it

31:40.460 --> 31:42.257
out of the news.
If they see you here...
It's my job, Eli.

31:42.300 --> 31:43.426
The governor wants to discuss

31:43.460 --> 31:44.597
the legal implications
of closing down

31:44.630 --> 31:45.927
the nearest cell tower.

31:45.970 --> 31:47.460
No, no, there are so many things

31:47.500 --> 31:48.432
wrong with that sentence.

31:48.470 --> 31:50.199
Just go home.
Hey, Ramona.

31:50.240 --> 31:51.605
You got a minute?

31:51.640 --> 31:53.267
Peter, no, you can't
be seen with her.

31:53.310 --> 31:54.607
That'll bring Ramona back
into the news.

31:54.640 --> 31:57.200
Just need ten minutes,
that's all.

31:57.240 --> 31:58.571
Can you give me
ten minutes, Pastor?

31:58.610 --> 32:00.100
Sure, Peter,
take the time you need.

32:02.050 --> 32:04.314
(car door closing)

32:05.490 --> 32:06.639
Dear God.

32:06.690 --> 32:08.157
Are you all right, Eli?

32:09.320 --> 32:11.356
No.

32:11.390 --> 32:13.381
I'm not.

32:13.430 --> 32:15.398
I just realize
that I work very hard,

32:15.430 --> 32:16.658
and I am not appreciated.

32:16.700 --> 32:18.520
You want to talk about it?

32:20.270 --> 32:22.067
Okay, we're back
in about ten minutes.

